The [[English language|English]] [[suffix]]es '''-cephalic''' and '''-cephaly''' means "relating to the head".  The most common use is in relation to the [[anatomy|anatomical]] [[head]], though words ending which such a suffix can also relate to [[head (disambiguation)|other meanings of "head"]].

There are many [[congenital disorder]]s relating to the head which are known as [[cephalic disorder]]s.

==Etymology==
The word ''cephalic'' has [[Latin language|Latin]] and [[Greek language|Greek]] origins: ''cephalicus'' and ''kephalikos'' respectively, both meaning "head".

